{"title_page": "2012\u201313 Montenegrin First League", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[Montenegrin First League]]\n| season             = 2012\u201313\n| winners            = [[FK Sutjeska Nik\u0161i\u0107|Sutjeska]] (1st title)\n| relegated          = [[FK Jedinstvo Bijelo Polje|Jedinstvo Bijelo Polje]]\n| continentalcup1    = [[2013\u201314 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifier = [[FK Sutjeska Nik\u0161i\u0107|Sutjeska]]\n| continentalcup2    = [[2013\u201314 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[FK \u010celik Nik\u0161i\u0107|\u010celik]]<br>[[FK Rudar Pljevlja|Rudar]]<br>[[FK Mladost Podgorica|Mladost]]\n| league topscorer   = Admir Adrovi\u0107<br />[[\u017darko Kora\u0107 (footballer)|\u017darko Kora\u0107]]<br />(15 goals)\n| biggest home win   = [[OFK Grbalj|Grbalj]] 4\u20130 [[FK Rudar Pljevlja|Rudar]]\n| biggest away win   = [[FK Lov\u0107en|Lov\u0107en]] 1\u20136 [[FK Sutjeska Nik\u0161i\u0107|Sutjeska]]\n| highest scoring    = [[FK Zeta|Zeta]] 3\u20134 [[OFK Petrovac]]<br />[[FK Lov\u0107en|Lov\u0107en]] 1\u20136 [[FK Sutjeska Nik\u0161i\u0107|Sutjeska]]\n| matches            = 198\n| total goals        = 485\n| longest wins       = 6 games<br />[[FK Sutjeska Nik\u0161i\u0107|Sutjeska]]\n| longest unbeaten   = 15 games<br />[[FK Budu\u0107nost Podgorica|Budu\u0107nost]]\n| longest losses     = 9 games<br />[[FK Mornar|Mornar]]\n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason         = [[2011\u201312 Montenegrin First League|2011\u201312]]\n| nextseason         = [[2013\u201314 Montenegrin First League|2013\u201314]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2012\u201313 [[Montenegrin First League]]''' was the seventh season of top-tier football in Montenegro. The season began on 11 August 2012 and ended on 1 June 2013. The mid-season winter break began on 2 December 2012 and ended on 7 March 2013. [[FK Budu\u0107nost Podgorica]] are the defending champions.\n\n==Teams==\nLast season, [[FK Bokelj|Bokelj]], [[FK Berane|Berane]], and [[FK De\u010di\u0107|De\u010di\u0107]] were relegated to the [[Montenegrin Second League]]. [[Montenegrin Cup]] winners [[FK \u010celik Nik\u0161i\u0107]] were promoted along with [[FK Mornar|Mornar]] and [[FK Jedinstvo Bijelo Polje|Jedinstvo Bijelo Polje]].\n\n=== Stadiums and locations ===\n{{Location map+|Montenegro|float=right|width=300|caption=Location of the 2012\u201313 Montenegrin First League teams|places=\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.376712 |long=18.751988 |label=[[FK Grbalj|Grbalj]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.38 |long=18.92 |label=[[FK Lov\u0107en|Lov\u0107en]] |position=right}}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.28 |long=18.83 |label=[[FK Mogren|Mogren]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.1 |long=19.1 |label=[[FK Mornar|Mornar]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.205556 |long=18.9425 |label=[[OFK Petrovac|Petrovac]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=43.04 |long=19.75 |label=[[FK Jedinstvo Bijelo Polje|Jedinstvo]] }}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.444805 |long=19.264441 |label=<!--Podgorica--> }}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.78 |long=18.94 |label=<!--Niksic--> }}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=43.36 |long=19.36 |label=[[FK Rudar Pljevlja|Rudar]] |position=left}}\n<!--DISPLAY FIX FOR NIKSIC CLUBS-->\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|mark=TransparentPlaceholder.png |lat=42.78 |long=18.94 |label=[[FK Sutjeska Nik\u0161i\u0107|Sutjeska]]<br />[[FK \u010celik Nik\u0161i\u0107|\u010celik]] }}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.335 |long=19.231111 |label=[[FK Zeta|Zeta]] |position=bottom}}\n<!--DISPLAY FIX FOR PODGORICA CLUBS-->\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|mark=TransparentPlaceholder.png |lat=42.5 |long=19.264441 |label=[[FK Budu\u0107nost Podgorica|Budu\u0107nost]]<br />[[FK Mladost Podgorica|Mladost]] }}\n}}\n\nAll figures for stadiums include '''seating''' capacity only, as many stadiums in Montenegro have stands without chairs which would otherwise be the actual number of people able to attend football matches not regulated by [[UEFA]] or [[FIFA]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Team\n! City\n! Stadium\n! Capacity\n|-\n|[[FK Budu\u0107nost Podgorica|Budu\u0107nost]]\n| [[Podgorica]]\n| [[Stadion Pod Goricom]]\n| align=\"center\" | 12,000<ref>[https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/FirstDiv/uefaorg/Publications/01/67/03/93/1670393_DOWNLOAD.pdf] UEFA Multimedia PDF file</ref>\n|-\n|[[FK \u010celik Nik\u0161i\u0107|\u010celik]]\n| [[Nik\u0161i\u0107]]\n| Stadion \u017deljezare\n| align=\"center\" | 1,000\n|-\n|[[FK Grbalj|Grbalj]]\n| [[Radanovi\u0107i, Kotor|Radanovi\u0107i]]\n| Stadion u Radanovi\u0107ima\n| align=\"center\" | 1,000\n|-\n|[[FK Jedinstvo Bijelo Polje|Jedinstvo]]\n| [[Bijelo Polje]]\n| [[Gradski stadion (Bijelo Polje)|City Stadium]]\n| align=\"center\" | 5,000\n|-\n|[[FK Lov\u0107en|Lov\u0107en]]\n| [[Cetinje]]\n| [[Stadion Obili\u0107a Poljana]]\n| align=\"center\" | 1,000\n|-\n|[[FK Mladost Podgorica|Mladost]]\n| Podgorica\n| [[Stadion Cvijetni Brijeg]]\n| align=\"center\" | 1,000\n|-\n|[[FK Mornar|Mornar]]\n| [[Bar, Montenegro|Bar]]\n| [[Stadion Topolica]]\n| align=\"center\" | 1,000\n|-\n|[[FK Mogren|Mogren]]\n| [[Budva]]\n| [[Stadion Lugovi]]\n| align=\"center\" | 2,000\n|-\n|[[OFK Petrovac]]\n| [[Petrovac, Montenegro|Petrovac]]\n| [[Stadion Pod Malim Brdom]]\n| align=\"center\" | 530<ref>[http://www.ofkpetrovac.com/index.php?strana=Stadion OFK Petrovac zvanicna stranica (Serbian) \u2013 Stadion pod Malim Brdom]</ref> \n|-\n|[[FK Rudar Pljevlja|Rudar]]\n| [[Pljevlja]]\n| [[Gradski stadion (Pljevlja)|Gradski stadion Pljevlja]]\n| align=\"center\" | 10,000\n|-\n|[[FK Sutjeska Nik\u0161i\u0107|Sutjeska]]\n| Nik\u0161i\u0107\n| [[Gradski stadion (Nik\u0161i\u0107)|Gradski stadion kraj Bistrice]]\n| align=\"center\" | 10,800<ref>[http://www.worldstadiums.com/europe/countries/montenegro.shtml World Stadiums \u2013 Countries \u2013 Europe \u2013 Montenegro]</ref>\n|-\n|[[FK Zeta|Zeta]]\n| [[Golubovci]]\n| [[Tre\u0161njica Stadium|Stadion Tre\u0161njica]]\n| align=\"center\" | 4,000\n|-\n|}\n\n==League table==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=QR\n\n|team1=SUT|name_SUT=[[FK Sutjeska Nik\u0161i\u0107|Sutjeska Nik\u0161i\u0107]]\n|team2=BUD|name_BUD=[[FK Budu\u0107nost Podgorica|Budu\u0107nost Podgorica]]\n|team3=\u010cEL|name_\u010cEL=[[FK \u010celik Nik\u0161i\u0107|\u010celik Nik\u0161i\u0107]]\n|team4=GRB|name_GRB=[[OFK Grbalj|Grbalj]]\n|team5=RUD|name_RUD=[[FK Rudar Pljevlja|Rudar Pljevlja]]\n|team6=MLA|name_MLA=[[OFK Titograd|Mladost Podgorica]]\n|team7=PET|name_PET=[[OFK Petrovac|Petrovac]]\n|team8=ZET|name_ZET=[[FK Zeta|Zeta]]\n|team9=LOV|name_LOV=[[FK Lov\u0107en|Lov\u0107en]]\n|team10=MOG|name_MOG=[[FK Mogren|Mogren]]\n|team11=MOR|name_MOR=[[FK Mornar|Mornar]]\n|team12=JED|name_JED=[[FK Jedinstvo Bijelo Polje|Jedinstvo Bijelo Polje]]\n|win_SUT=20|draw_SUT=5|loss_SUT=8|gf_SUT=50|ga_SUT=31|status_SUT=C\n|win_BUD=17|draw_BUD=9|loss_BUD=7|gf_BUD=57|ga_BUD=38\n|win_\u010cEL=15|draw_\u010cEL=8|loss_\u010cEL=10|gf_\u010cEL=41|ga_\u010cEL=35\n|win_GRB=13|draw_GRB=12|loss_GRB=8|gf_GRB=41|ga_GRB=21\n|win_RUD=15|draw_RUD=6|loss_RUD=12|gf_RUD=42|ga_RUD=40\n|win_MLA=9|draw_MLA=12|loss_MLA=12|gf_MLA=39|ga_MLA=48\n|win_PET=8|draw_PET=14|loss_PET=11|gf_PET=36|ga_PET=42\n|win_ZET=8|draw_ZET=13|loss_ZET=12|gf_ZET=43|ga_ZET=45\n|win_LOV=11|draw_LOV=4|loss_LOV=18|gf_LOV=36|ga_LOV=52\n|win_MOG=10|draw_MOG=7|loss_MOG=16|gf_MOG=33|ga_MOG=42|adjust_points_MOG=-1|status_MOG=O\n|win_MOR=9|draw_MOR=9|loss_MOR=15|gf_MOR=36|ga_MOR=47|status_MOR=O\n|win_JED=9|draw_JED=9|loss_JED=15|gf_JED=31|ga_JED=45|status_JED=R\n\n|note_MOG=[[FK Mogren|Mogren]] were deducted 1 point.\n\n|col_CL2=green1|text_CL2=Qualification to [[2013\u201314 UEFA Champions League#Second qualifying round|Champions League second qualifying round]]\n|result1=CL2\n|col_EXCL=inherit|text_EXCL=Excluded from European competitions \n|note_res_EXCL=Budu\u0107nost Podgorica won the [[2012\u201313 Montenegrin Cup]], so the other UEFA Europa League spots initially shifted down. Budu\u0107nost and Grbalj were excluded from participating in UEFA club competitions for the next season after FSCG denied them an UEFA license.<ref>{{cite news|title=Saop\u0161tenje Komisije za \u017ealbe za licenciranje FSCG \u2013 03.06.2013 |url=http://fscg.co.me/201306033065/Vijesti-Savez/saoptenje-komisije-za-albe-fscg-03062013.html |publisher=[[UEFA]] |date=3 June 2013 |accessdate=4 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130608061955/http://fscg.co.me/201306033065/Vijesti-Savez/saoptenje-komisije-za-albe-fscg-03062013.html |archivedate=8 June 2013 }}</ref>\n|result2=EXCL|result4=EXCL\n|col_EL1=blue1|text_EL1=Qualification to [[2013\u201314 UEFA Europa League#First qualifying round|Europa League first qualifying round]] \n|note_res_EL1=EXCL\n|result3=EL1|result5=EL1|result6=EL1\n|col_RP=red2|text_RP=Qualification to [[#Relegation play-offs|relegation play-offs]]\n|result10=RP|result11=RP\n|col_R=red1|text_R=Relegation to [[2013\u201314 Montenegrin Second League|Montenegrin Second League]]\n|result12=R\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) goal difference; 3) number of goals scored.\n|update=complete\n|source=[http://fscg.co.me/T-Com-1.CFL.html fscg.co.me]\n}}\n\n==Results==\nThe schedule consisted of three rounds. During the first two rounds, each team played each other once home and away for a total of 22 matches. The pairings of the third round were then set according to the standings after the first two rounds, giving every team a third game against each opponent for a total of 33 games per team.\n\n===First and second round===\n{{#invoke:Sports results|main\n|matches_style=FBR|solid_cell=grey\n|team1=BUD|team2=\u010cEL|team3=GRB|team4=JED|team5=LOV\n|team6=MLA|team7=MOR|team8=MOG|team9=PET|team10=RUD\n|team11=SUT|team12=ZET\n\n|name_BUD=[[FK Budu